President Obama has welcomed the announcement that Colombian President Santos reached a framework for peace negotiations between the Colombian government and the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC). This framework sets the stage for talks that aim to end the 50-year conflict with the FARC and allow Colombians to live with greater peace, security, and prosperity. President Obama recognizes the commitment of the Santos administration to seeking peace and acknowledges the courage and sacrifice of the Colombian people in achieving this milestone. The statement also calls on the FARC to seize this opportunity to end terrorism and narcotics trafficking. The United States reaffirms its partnership with Colombia in defense, security, and promoting citizen security, human rights, and economic prosperity.